 this page</button></div><div class=3D"theme-doc-markdown markdown"><h1>Sel=
f Hosting</h1><p>Logflare can be self-hosted. As of now, only a single mach=
ine setup is supported.</p><p>Two different backends are supported:</p><ul>=
<li>BigQuery</li><li>PostgreSQL (experimental)</li></ul><p>Docker-compose i=
s the recommended way to manage single node deployments.</p><h3 class=3D"an=
chor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"limitations">Limitations<a hr=
ef=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#limitations" class=3D"hash-li=
nk" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Limitations" title=3D"Direct link to Limit=
ations">=E2=80=8B</a></h3><p>Inviting team users and other team-related fun=
ctionality is currently not supported, as Logflare self-hosted is currently=
 intended for single-user experience only.</p><p>All browser authentication=
 will be disabled when in single-tenant mode.</p><h2 class=3D"anchor anchor=
WithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"configuration">Configuration<a href=3D"h=
ttps://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#configuration" class=3D"hash-link" a=
ria-label=3D"Direct link to Configuration" title=3D"Direct link to Configur=
ation">=E2=80=8B</a></h2><h3 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_W=
Yt5" id=3D"common-configuration">Common Configuration<a href=3D"https://doc=
s.logflare.app/self-hosting/#common-configuration" class=3D"hash-link" aria=
-label=3D"Direct link to Common Configuration" title=3D"Direct link to Comm=
on Configuration">=E2=80=8B</a></h3><table><thead><tr><th>Env Var</th><th>T=
ype</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>LOGFLARE_DB_E=
NCRYPTION_KEY</code></td><td>Base64 encryption key, <strong>required</stron=
g></td><td>Encryption key used for encrypting sensitive data.</td></tr><tr>=
<td><code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY_RETIRED</code></td><td>Base64 encrypti=
on key, defaults to <code>nil</code></td><td>The deprecated encryption key =
to migrate existing database secrets from. Data will be migrated to the key=
 set under <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code>. Used for encryption key=
 rolling only.</td></tr><tr><td><code>LOGFLARE_SINGLE_TENANT</code></td><td=
>Boolean, defaults to <code>false</code></td><td>If enabled, a singular use=
r will be seeded. All browser usage will default to the user.</td></tr><tr>=
<td><code>LOGFLARE_API_KEY</code></td><td>string, defaults to <code>nil</co=
de></td><td><strong>Deprecated</strong>. Use <code>LOGFLARE_PUBLIC_ACCESS_T=
OKEN</code> instead. Alias for <code>LOGFLARE_PUBLIC_ACCESS_TOKEN</code>.</=
td></tr><tr><td><code>LOGFLARE_PUBLIC_ACCESS_TOKEN</code></td><td>string, d=
efaults to <code>nil</code></td><td>If set, creates a public access token f=
or the provisioned user, for ingestion or querying usage. Single-tenant mod=
e only.</td></tr><tr><td><code>LOGFLARE_PRIVATE_ACCESS_TOKEN</code></td><td=
>string, defaults to <code>nil</code></td><td>If set, creates a private acc=
ess token for the provisioned user, for management API usage. Single-tenant=
