ES_BACKEND_SCHEMA</code></td><td>string, optional, defaults to <code>public=
</code></td><td>Specifies the database schema to scope all operations.</td>=
</tr></tbody></table><h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5"=
 id=3D"database-encryption">Database Encryption<a href=3D"https://docs.logf=
lare.app/self-hosting/#database-encryption" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=
=3D"Direct link to Database Encryption" title=3D"Direct link to Database En=
cryption">=E2=80=8B</a></h2><p>Certain database columns that store sensitiv=
e data are encrypted with the <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code> key.
Encryption keys must be Base64 encoded.</p><p>Cipher used is AES with a 256=
-bit key in GCM mode.</p><p>If <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code> envi=
ronement variable is not provided, a default hardcoded encryption key will =
be used.</p><h3 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"ro=
lling-encryption-keys">Rolling Encryption Keys<a href=3D"https://docs.logfl=
are.app/self-hosting/#rolling-encryption-keys" class=3D"hash-link" aria-lab=
el=3D"Direct link to Rolling Encryption Keys" title=3D"Direct link to Rolli=
ng Encryption Keys">=E2=80=8B</a></h3><p>In order to roll encryption keys a=
nd migrate existing encrypted data, use the <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KE=
Y_RETIRED</code> environment variable.</p><p>Steps to perform the migration=
 are:</p><ol><li>Move the retired encryption key from <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENC=
RYPTION_KEY</code> to <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY_RETIRED</code>.</li>=
<li>Generate a new encryption key and set it to <code>LOGFLARE_DB_ENCRYPTIO=
N_KEY</code>.</li><li>Restart or deploy the server with the new environment=
 variables.</li><li>Upon successful server startup, an <code>info</code> lo=
g will be emitted that says that an retired encryption key is detected, and=
 the migration will be initiated to transition all data encrypted with the =
retired key to be encrypted with the new key.</li><li>Once the migration is=
 complete, the retired encryption key can be safely removed. There will be =
an <code>info</code> log that will be emitted once the migration is complet=
e.</li></ol><h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"bi=
gquery-setup">BigQuery Setup<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosti=
ng/#bigquery-setup" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to BigQue=
ry Setup" title=3D"Direct link to BigQuery Setup">=E2=80=8B</a></h2><h3 cla=
ss=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"pre-requisites">Pre-r=
equisites<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#pre-requisites"=
 class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Pre-requisites" title=3D"=
Direct link to Pre-requisites">=E2=80=8B</a></h3><p>You will need a Google =
Cloud project <strong>with billing enabled</strong> in order to proceed.</p=
><p>The requirements for server startup are as follows after creating the p=
roject:</p><ul><li>Project ID</li><li>Project number</li><li>A service acco=
unt key</li></ul><h4 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=
=3D"setting-up-bigquery-service-account">Setting up BigQuery Service Accoun=
t<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#setting-up-bigquery-ser=
vice-account" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Setting up B=
igQuery Service Account" title=3D"Direct link to Setting up BigQuery Servic=
e Account">=E2=80=8B</a></h4><p>To ensure that you have sufficient permissi=
ons to insert into your Google Cloud BigQuery, ensure that you have created=
 a service account with either:</p><ul><li>BigQuery Admin role; or</li><li>=
The following permissions:<ul><li>bigquery.datasets.create</li><li>bigquery=
.datasets.get</li><li>bigquery.datasets.getIamPolicy</li><li>bigquery.datas=
ets.update</li><li>bigquery.jobs.create</li><li>bigquery.routines.create</l=
i><li>bigquery.routines.update</li><li>bigquery.tables.create</li><li>bigqu=
ery.tables.delete</li><li>bigquery.tables.get</li><li>bigquery.tables.getDa=
ta</li><li>bigquery.tables.update</li><li>bigquery.tables.updateData</li></=
ul></li></ul><p>We recommend setting the BigQuery Admin role, as it simplif=
ies permissions setup.</p><h4 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_=
WYt5" id=3D"obtaining-the-bigquery-service-account-key">Obtaining the BigQu=
ery Service Account Key<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#o=
btaining-the-bigquery-service-account-key" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=
=3D"Direct link to Obtaining the BigQuery Service Account Key" title=3D"Dir=
ect link to Obtaining the BigQuery Service Account Key">=E2=80=8B</a></h4><=
p>In order for Logflare to connect sources to their relevant BigQuery table=
s, we would need to have a service account key that can sign the JWTs neede=
d to authenticate with the Google Cloud APIs.</p><p>To obtain the BigQuery =
service account key after creating it, navigate to IAM &gt; Service Account=
s in the web console and click on the "Manage Keys" action option.</p><p><i=
mg loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Service Account List Manage Keys Action" src=3D"=
https://docs.logflare.app/assets/images/service-account-mange-keys-5c985465=
e80e1b53b74635e6449cf781.png" width=3D"979" height=3D"502" class=3D"img_ev3=
q"></p><p>Thereafter, click on "Add Key" to create a new key. The key will =
be in a JSON format. Store this key securely on your host machine.</p><p><i=
mg loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Add Key Button" src=3D"https://docs.logflare.app=
/assets/images/add-key-a94a21adc48925863bf72a23ac48cc93.png" width=3D"986" =
height=3D"445" class=3D"img_ev3q"></p><p>You can also obtain the key via th=
e <code>gcloud</code> cli by following the <a href=3D"https://cloud.google.=
com/iam/docs/keys-create-delete" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferr=
er">official documentation</a>.</p><h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScro=
llNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"deployment-with-docker-compose">Deployment with Docker=
 Compose<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/#deployment-with-=
docker-compose" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to Deployment=
 with Docker Compose" title=3D"Direct link to Deployment with Docker Compos=
e">=E2=80=8B</a></h2><p>Using docker compose is the <strong>recommended met=
hod</strong> for self-hosting.</p><ol><li>Create the <code>docker-compose.y=
