 for legacy reasons and is mostly for compatibility with older Logflare lib=
raries.</p><h2 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id=3D"ope=
ntelemetry">OpenTelemetry<a href=3D"https://docs.logflare.app/self-hosting/=
#opentelemetry" class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to OpenTeleme=
try" title=3D"Direct link to OpenTelemetry">=E2=80=8B</a></h2><p>To deploy =
OpenTelemetry to Cloudflare + GCP successfully, the following need to be ac=
complished:</p><ol><li>Expose instance group named port 50051 (or whatever =
it is set on the server.)</li><li>Set load balancer to send <code>otel.logf=
lare.app:443</code> to the above named port on the designated backend. Back=
end must be set to HTTP/2 protocol.</li><li>Between instances and load bala=
ncer, connections need to be TLS encrypted. Can be self-signed. Generate se=
lf-signed certs with <code>make ssl.prod</code> and <code>make ssl.staging<=
/code>. No CA cert needs to be used when self-signing, can use public certs=
.</li><li>Between CF and GCP, connections should have Full SSL (optionally =
strict). Generate an origin cert on CF and use it on the load balancer. SSL=
 is terminated at the load balancer.</li><li>Connecting client should not n=
eed an SSL cert to connect (unless you want to encrypt the traffic between =
client and instance)</li></ol><h3 class=3D"anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNav=
bar_WYt5" id=3D"otel-troubleshooting">OTel Troubleshooting<a href=3D"https:=
